ired for public governance thus conceived. This includes the creation of various types of spaces for deep dialogue and mutual inquiry. This book demonstrates how this innovative vision would transform our current conceptions of governance.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aDeliberative Demokratie. 4aDirekte Demokratie. 4aEntscheidungsfindung. 4aGleichberechtigung. 4aKonsens. 4aPartizipatorische Demokratie. 4aPolitischer Dialog. 4aÖffentliche Verwaltung. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aConsensus-Building.  aDecision-Making.  aDialogue.  aEqual Value of Persons.  aParticipatory Deliberative Democracy.  aPublic Governance.1 aGill, Scherto, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut0 cEPUBz97831112407180 cprintz978311124052740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783111240596zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111240596zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111240596/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA